{{orphan|date=March 2016}}
{{notability|date=August 2017}}
'''John Belcher''' ([[floruit|fl.]] 1721-1763) was a Welsh [[Methodist]] preacher. His father, Edmund Belcher, of [[Eglwys Ilan]], was a local smith, and John himself initially joined him in the trade. By 1743 however he was working with the Watford Association. In 1744 he became an assistant of [[Howel Harris]]. He then was directed to tour North Wales. He enlisted in the army in 1758. His date of death is uncertain, but believed to be sometime after 1763.<ref>{{cite web|title=John Belcher|url=http://yba.llgc.org.uk/en/s-BELC-JOH-1721.html|website=Dictionary of Welsh Biography|publisher=National Library of Wales|accessdate=22 March 2016}}</ref>

